   <refentry id="ochad">
      <refentryinfo>
         <date>2005-07-27</date>
         <productname>ocha</productname>
         <title>ochad</title>
      </refentryinfo>

      <refmeta>              
         <refentrytitle>ochad</refentrytitle>
         <manvolnum>1</manvolnum>
      </refmeta>

      <refnamediv>   
         <refname>ochad</refname>
         <refpurpose>Ocha daemon</refpurpose>
      </refnamediv>

      <refsynopsisdiv>
	<title>Synopsis</title>
	<cmdsynopsis>
	  <command>ochad</command>
	  <arg choice="opt" rep="repeat">standard gnome arguments</arg>
	</cmdsynopsis>
      </refsynopsisdiv>

      <refsect1>
	<title>Description</title> 
	<para>
	  This is the ocha daemon. It'll listen for the key accelerator
	  and open the query window when it is pressed.
	  See ocha's GNOME documentation for details.
	</para>
	<para>
	  <command>ochad</command> registers itself to
	  the GNOME session managers and makes sure it'll be
	  restarted automatically next time the current user
	  logs in.
	</para>
	<para>
	  If you don't use the GNOME session manager, you'll need
	  to start the ocha daemon every time you log in. This might
	  be done by adding the command <userinput>ochad&amp;</userinput> to
	  <filename>~/.xinitrc</filename> or <filename>~/.Xsession</filename>
	</para>
      </refsect1>

